Task 3.2 Round 1 is complete. Here's what was built:

**LLM Visibility Simulator** — 4 new routes with a research-calibrated simulation engine:

1. **`/simulate`** — Setup page with industry presets (CRM, PM, Email, Hosting), brand/competitor/query inputs, model selection (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity), and samples config
2. **`/simulate/results`** — Brand visibility rankings table with Share of Model (SoM), avg position, sentiment breakdown, per-model rates, and sample response snippets
3. **`/simulate/compare`** — Side-by-side model comparison bars, model divergence table (best vs worst model per brand), cross-model agreement analysis
4. **`/simulate/trends`** — Historical run tracking with localStorage persistence (up to 20 runs), per-model trend tables, clickable history

**Key technical decisions:**
- Simulation engine uses seeded PRNG for deterministic results calibrated against research (ChatGPT ~3.5 brands/response, Perplexity ~13, 15% variance, 12% cross-model overlap)
- React Context provider shares state across all 4 route pages via a client-side layout
- All numbers trace back to approved Research 2.1, 2.2, 2.4 findings

**Build: SUCCESS** — zero errors, zero warnings, 16 routes generated.
